body:
`.grid-editor-container` has print-specific layout rules, but that class is not applied anywhere in the repository (search shows it only exists in this CSS). As a result, the intended `break-inside: avoid` and border styling won’t apply to the actual grid markup during print.

**AI-Optimized Suggestion:** In `app/print.css`, retarget these rules to a selector that exists (e.g., `[data-testid="groove-grid"]` or a dedicated class added to `GrooveGridEditor`’s outer container), so grid blocks reliably avoid page breaks in print/PDF.
```suggestion
    .grid-editor-container,
    [data-testid="groove-grid"] {
      break-inside: avoid;
      page-break-inside: avoid;
```

